        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1637873444" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4982447559465128184">When the US President calls Mary Ashley, a university professor to offer an ambassadorship to a country she was attached to, Romania, she surprises herself refusing the offer. Her husband is practicing medicine and moving to another country without his and the children, isn&apos;t worth any dreams. <br/><br/>But after her husband&apos;s sudden and mysterious death, she isn&apos;t left with any choice other than accepting the ambassadorship. She comes under the public&apos;s scrutinizing gaze, never allowed to make mistakes, </span>
  <span id="freeText4982447559465128184" style="display:none">When the US President calls Mary Ashley, a university professor to offer an ambassadorship to a country she was attached to, Romania, she surprises herself refusing the offer. Her husband is practicing medicine and moving to another country without his and the children, isn't worth any dreams. <br /><br />But after her husband's sudden and mysterious death, she isn't left with any choice other than accepting the ambassadorship. She comes under the public's scrutinizing gaze, never allowed to make mistakes, her every move being noted and meticulously inspected. She never thought her job could be a turning point in her life. Soon, her life is in danger, from forces she doesn't understand. Her decision to write history seems trivial when the matter is of life and death. <br /><br />This is one of those books that will uplift your mood, just to praise how intelligent and dedicated patriotic the protagonist was. Her knowledge and interest in Romanian culture can inspire anyone. </span>
  <a data-text-id="4982447559465128184" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
